args: You've gotta seriously be one with the\nwater to land that kinda move—not to\nmention totally fearless! He is PRO-tier!
Guess he was for real when he said he's\n＂nature itself.＂ Makes me wish I could\nbe a cat ridin' tandem with him!
Hm. At a glance, the skies look clear,\nand yet... Yes, I can feel it.
My apologies. Your safety is paramount,\nlittle one, so I am afraid we must cut\nour time short and head back.
Yo! You're back sooner than I was expec—
Oof, it is MAD choppy all of a sudden...\nWait, no way. Dude, don't tell me you\nsomehow predicted that'd happen!

In attaining revelation, I have become as
nature itself. The sea is but a part of me.
Thus, I can perceive an omen of ill
weather as simply as I draw breath.
Gah ha ha! Unbelievable!\nYou're outta this world, my dude!
Welp, guess we oughta call it a day.\nGotta hurry and get the cats back to\nmy beach hut before the sky breaks open.
What?! How'd you—\nErr, forget that. You say you're\nlooking for a skinny black cat?
What do you know?\nTell me, please!
Saw him just recently,\nas luck would have it.
He's in the village due north of here.\nYeah, that's the one.
Uh, have a nice trip! ...Bah, he can't\nhear me. He's already a mile away.
Yeah. Boy, that must be one important cat.\nOh well!
Long as we got him far away from here,\nwe're golden.
Now we just gots to get the surfin' cat\nto that rich so-and-so what wants it.\nPsh. This job ain't no sweat at all.
Hey, what say we start plannin' what\nwe're gonna do with the reward?
Whoa, let's not get ahead of ourselves,\nbub! Heh, not that I'm one to talk—\nI already got myself this little piece.
Ohhh, that's a nice necklace!\nMaybe I'll get one too!
